<title>FINLAND: AMER SAYS K-OWNERS TAKE LORD MOYNE'S OFFER.</title>
<headline>AMER SAYS K-OWNERS TAKE LORD MOYNE'S OFFER.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Finnish sport goods group Amer-Yhtyma Oy said on Tuesday British investor Lord Moyne's offer to acquire voting control of the company had been approved by three of the four Finnish institutions owning vote-heavy K-shares.  </p>
<p>According to the terms of the offer, Jonathan Bryan Guinness, third Lord Moyne, should announce by June 30 exactly how many K-shares he intended to buy.</p>
<p>On June 2, Lord Moyne offered to buy 1.1 million K-shares for 301 million markka and acquire over 58 percednt of votes in Amer.</p>
<p>Representatives of the four institutions said on June 13 they would not consider a later competing bid by Finnish investment company Norvestia .</p>
